Title: QI - Portal Registration, Sign-In, Multi Factor Authentication(MFA), Account Management
Tags: Portal; Release 1.0; Reusable Portal form for Impacted individuals(students) submissions
Description:
Feature Statement/ Description:
This feature involves the authentication of the Impacted Individual:
  • when setting up a portal user account i.e. registering to use the portal,
  • when logging into portal to submit the portal submission form,
  • when updating profile information i.e. first name, last name, email address and mobile number,
  • when changing their portal password 

Dependencies 
  • The design of the Portal form including UX
  • ASQA is dependent on the DEWR technical team for the following regarding QI authentication:
    • Network changes 
    • Azure infra changes 
    • Azure B2C changes
NOTE: The above detailed changes are documented in the Authentication run sheet per link: 
Assumptions
  • DEWR will provide the above required changes by the required dates 
Stakeholders
  • External entity (Impacted Individual)
  • ASQA Executives
  • ASQA Qualifications Integrity team
  • ASQA Digital Publishing team
  • Regulatory teams
  • Service Delivery
  • Operations Support
Technical Design or Architecture:
  • Technical design and Architecture artefacts are filed on SharePoint here: Functional and Technical Design
  • The Azure B2C Deployment Runsheet is filed here: Azure B2C Deployment Runsheet
Acceptance Criteria:
The functionality below will be designed and implemented for the DTP QI Release 1 in August 2025:
  • The portal supports the following:
    • Authentication of Impacted Individuals:
      • when they register to use the portal and set up their user account
      • when they access the link in the NOI email to complete their submission form
    • Identification of Impacted Individuals via their ASQA Registration Number (ARN) and Date of Birth (DOB)
    • On signing up to the portal, the Impacted Individuals portal user account is linked to their ARMS contact record
    • The system sets up the Impacted Individuals primary email address during sign up to the portal

The functionality below will be designed and implemented for the DTP QI Release 2 after August 2025:
  • The Impacted Individuals can successfully change/update the following in the portal:
    • their first name and last name 
    • their email address
    • their mobile number

Title: Implement Student Signup Prototype
Description:
Complete end to end functional prototype that includes
  • Sinning up by clicking a link that lands the user in Azure B2C signup first
    • Azure AD signup will verify email, identify user as a student using URN and DOB, allow set a password, creates a B2C account with a ASQA customer id
    • Rejects re-signup using same URN and DOB
  • Then lands on the QI form with enough information to load RTOs and Quals for the student
  • Student can sign in again to the QI form

Title: Authenticate B2C to Web API and Web API to Dataverse
Description:
Student signup in Azure B2C needs to identify user as a valid student.

This can be done by Azure B2C calling HTTP endpoint of a Web API to validate student ARN and DOB against Dataverse.

To achieve the above Azure B2C needs to needs to authenticate to the Web API

Web API app registration and API permissions - Microsoft identity platform | Microsoft Learn

To achieve the above Web API needs to needs to authenticate to Dataverse. Therefore a App Registration with a secret and access to Dataverse is required - DONE

  • Stop re-signup already signed up students
  • Allow student to change the primary email and the sign in email

Title: Implement CAPTCHA for Sign Up
QI - Impacted Individual profile updates (update email address, first name, last name and mobile number)
Description:
As an Impacted Individual

I require the ability to update my portal profile credentials i.e. email, first name, last name and mobile number

So that:
  • I receive all ASQA QI emails to the correct email address i.e. NOI and NOD email
  • My correct first and last name(surname) is used on all notifications and emails received from ASQA
  • I receive all SMS's sent by ASQA to my correct mobile number i.e. portal registration, NOI and NOD SMS's

Business Context/ Benefits: 
Impacted Individuals may be required to supply ASQA with their updated profile credentials i.e. their email address, first name, last name and mobile number.
The Impacted Individuals profile credentials are required for ASQA to successfully send Impacted Individuals the NOI and NOD emails, SMS's (initial portal registration, NOI and NOD SMS's).


Design considerations:
Dinuka, please insert design notes here

Assumptions (if any): 

N/A

Business Rules (if any): 
  • Impacted Individuals can ONLY change their profile credentials after their ARMS contact record is created from the Master List upload
Question: Is the Impacted Individual limited in changing their profile credentials at any time in the workflow?

Dependencies: 
  • N/A
Acceptance Criteria:
1.Impacted Individual profile updates in portal
Given an Impacted Individual requires to update their profile credentials i.e. email address, first name, last name and mobile number
When the Impacted Individual successfully signs into the portal
Then they will be able to update and save their email address, first name, last name and mobile number credentials

2.Impacted Individuals profile updating email
Given an Impacted Individual has changed and updated their profile credentials in the portal 
When the Impacted Individual successfully saves these changes
Then they will receive an email notifying them that their ASQA profile credential have been successfully updated

3. ARMS Impacted Individual contact record updating 
Given an Impacted Individual has changed and updated their profile credentials in the portal 
When the Impacted Individual successfully saves these changes
Then the Impacted Individual ARMS contact record will be updated with their updated profile credentials

Title: QI - Ability for the Impacted Individual to update their Primary Email and Primary Mobile Phone (Self-Service)
Description:
As an ASQA portal registered impacted individual
I want to self-service and update my primary email and primary mobile number that I originally registered with on the portal
so that I can keep my registered contact information up to date.

Design Consideration

Impacts B2C and Power Pages.
B2C - Custom Policy and Web API
Power Page - Re-direction to B2C Policies

The Primary Email / Primary Mobile Number in B2C is auto-updated to the new information provided by the impacted individual.
The Primary Email / Primary Mobile Number in D365 Contact is auto-updated to the new information provided by the impacted individual.

Assumption

No updates allowable to the primary email and primary mobile number in the Contact record in D365 for portal registered contact. Covered in #9219
Acceptance Criteria:
1.Update option on Profile Page

Given the impacted individual is signed into the ASQA portal
When they navigate to the Profile Page
And click on update Primary Email Address or Primary Mobile Number.
They will be redirected to Azure B2C to update Primary Email Address or Primary Mobile Number
And can update their Primary Email Address and Primary Mobile Number.

2. Synchronisation of Contact Information
Given the impacted individual was redirected to B2C to Primary Email or Primary Mobile
When the impacted individual successfully updates the Primary Email or Primary Mobile 
Then the corresponding fields in both B2C user profile and D365 contact record are automatically updated to reflect the new information.
And the impacted individual will be redirected back to the Profile page of the portal

Title: QI - Impacted Individual portal registration NO DOB error message
Description:
As an Impacted Individual registering for the portal, 

I require the ability to use my ARN (received in my NOI email) and my date of birth to complete my registration

So that I can securely access the portal. 

And If my date of birth is not on record, 

I require to be informed and guided to contact Service Delivery 

So that Service Delivery can help rectify and add the date of birth for me. 

Business Context/ Benefits: 
Impacted Individuals are required when registering to use their provided ARN (form NOI) and date of birth. 
It may occur that Impacted Individuals may not have a date of birth associated to their contact record and therefore, they will be required to contact ASQA's Service Desk under certain circumstances to add their date of birth against their contact record in CRM. 

Design considerations:
Error message text 'There is no date of birth associated with this record. Please contact ASQA for assistance.'

Assumptions: 
  • Impacted Individual has received an NOI with an ARN 
  • The portal is accessible and the registration page is available 
  • The Impacted Individual's contact record may or may not have a date of birth associated in the CRM system
Acceptance Criteria:
Scenario: No date of birth associated with contact record who has ARN 

Given I am an impacted individual who has received an ARN in my NOI via email 
And there is no date of birth associated with my contact record and ARN record in the CRM system 
When I enter my ARN and date of birth into the portal registration 
Then an error message is displayed stating "There is no date of birth associated with this record. Please contact ASQA for assistance."

Title: Set Default Country Code to +61 on Mobile-authenticated Registration Page
Description:
As an impacted individual registering for the ASQA portal and through the mobile-authenticated page
I want the area code to default to Australia (+61)
so that I do not have to manually change it from the United States during sign-up.
Acceptance Criteria:
Given the impacted individual is on the mobile-authenticated registration page for the portal
When the page is displayed
Then the default area code should be set to +61 (Australia).

Title: QI - Portal to SharePoint/App - Evidence File Upload Issues
Description:
Summary

  • Multiple UAT users are experiencing issues with file upload. Issues particularly regarding viewing uploaded large files (display of uploaded items in SharePoint and the application) and upload timing out on portal due to uploading large files.

The items listed below can be found in the QI UAT Incident Log.

QI UAT Incident Log.xlsx

Filter column P by 'Triage Closed - Referred - ASQA/DEWR


Consolidated Main Issues

  1. Missing files in SharePoint/app after successful upload
    • Users report that especially large files (MP4s, ZIPs) are shown as ‘successfully uploaded’ but do not appear in SharePoint or under the relevant case in the application
    • This can display as a partial file upload, where only some files (smaller files) appear
    • Related Incident log no. 5, 6, 7, 9, 10, 16, 24, 26
  2. Large File upload Failures
    • Users report uploads for large files (ex. 480mb, 1.3GB and greater) have timed out within minutes, or provide a session expiry error message
    • Related Incident log no. 11, 13, 18, 19
  3. Missing file format
    • User reported missing file type format .msg
    • Related Incident log no. 4

 

Dependencies

  • The fix is referred to ASQA for review.


Related

  • #8803

And the email verification is not successfully

Then an error message is displayed indicating the email

is already in use

And I cannot proceed with sign-up

And I must re-enter a unique email address

 

PASSED Scenario 10: User leaves sign-up flow before completing

mobile MFA setup

successfully verified my identity and created an ASQA portal account

And I have not completed my mobile number Multi

Factor Authentication (MFA) setup

When I close or navigate away from my web

browser before the MFA is configured

Then my account is marked as incomplete for MFA

And I am not granted access to the portal

 

PASSED Scenario 11: User attempts to signs into portal

without completing MFA setup 

Given I am an Impacted Individual that has an

ASQA portal account but has not completed my mobile number MFA setup

When I attempt to sign into the portal

Then I am redirected to my mobile MFA setup step

And I must successfully configure my mobile MFA before

being granted access to the portal

 

 

PASSED 1. Scenario: Impacted Individual completes successful portal sign-in with valid email and password

Given I am an Impacted Individual on the portal sign-in page

When I enter my valid email address captured at their portal registration 

And I enter my valid password captured at the portal their registration

And I am multi factor authenticated

Then I will be will successfully signed into the ASQA portal

Title: [NOC] Prototype End to End 100 Points ID Verification
Description:
Please refer to the following link for high level technical design.

100 Points ID Check.loop

Scope of the prototype:
  • Portal to intercept the sign and signup and enforce the user to complete the signup. For example, if the signed in or signed up CEO hasn't completed the 100 points ID check or fit and proper form enforce them to complete. For this task only 100 points ID check in play.
  • Portal to redirect user to 100 points ID check B2C policy
  • 100 points ID check B2C policy redirect to myGovID
  • B2C to save Digital ID info after successful response from myGovID
  • Portal to redirect the user to and alternative ID verification process after error response from myGovID (i.e. Digital ID does not match the required ID strength)
